parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The windshield leak can cause water to enter the vehicle, leading to electrical damage, distracting the driver, and potentially causing accidents. The detachment of the windshield can also cause injury or accident if it comes apart while driving.
symptoms: Water leaking into the vehicle through the windshield
water pooling in the interior dome light areas
water splashing onto the gear shifter
and electrical issues such as non-functional lights on the gear shifter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the subframe can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to potential safety risks, including loss of control or collapse of the vehicle.
symptoms: premature corrosion near the front exhaust
and weakening of the subframe structure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield adhesive can cause the windshield to detach from the body, leading to water leaks, reduced visibility, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: windshield comes away from the body
and reduced visibility due to water or debris entering the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SRS system can disable the airbags, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The "SRS Airbag Failure Urgent" message appears on the dashboard
the airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash.
